cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.IT. 

The paper proposes an information theoretic analysis of classification for deep neural network structures, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNN). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper focuses on image classification tasks. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of transfer learning, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a principled information theoretic analysis, which aligns with the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory).
